  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, combine seafood stock, fish sauce, coconut sugar, grated ginger, and garlic. Whisk until the sugar dissolves.",
    "Add the brown rice to the bowl and mix until the rice is well coated with the seafood mixture.",
    "Add the shrimp and scallops to the bowl and toss until they are evenly coated with the seafood mixture.",
    "Transfer the seafood and rice mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Sprinkle toasted coconut flakes and chopped green onions on top of the seafood mixture.",
    "Return the dish to the oven and bake for an additional 5-7 minutes, or until the coconut flakes are lightly toasted.",
    "Remove the dish from the oven and season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the dish hot, garnished with additional green onions if desired."
  ],
